  "body": "A set of recommended labels around applications just landed in the Kubernetes docs. They can be seen at https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/common-labels/. Helm also has a set of standard labels in the best practices section at https://docs.helm.sh/chart_best_practices/#standard-labels. Many of these are for the same thing but with a different name.\r\n\r\nHere's a diff of the two:\r\n\r\n| Helm | k8s |\r\n| --- | --- |\r\n| `heritage` | `app.kubernetes.io/managed-by` |\r\n| `release` | `app.kubernetes.io/instance` |\r\n| `chart` | - |\r\n| `app` | - |\r\n| `component` | `app.kubernetes.io/component` |\r\n| - | `app.kubernetes.io/name` |\r\n| - | `app.kubernetes.io/version` |\r\n| - | `app.kubernetes.io/part-of` |\r\n\r\nNote, the use of a prefix of `app.kubernetes.io` is because these are not private and we expect machines to do work with these. For those cases k8s uses the notion of namespacing them.\r\n\r\nMore details on the k8s ones are in the docs. With examples.\r\n\r\nHow should we handle this for Helm and Charts?",
